<h2>Information Architecture</h2>
<h3>Discussion</h3>
<p>We'll take a look at the basic <strong>Information Architecture (IA)</strong> that will make up your Sitecore solution and how planning in the early stages plays a key role to your solution's success.  In the case of this solution, our Inforamtion Architecture is very simple and should look somethig like this.</p>
<p><strong>Home</strong></p>
<p><strong>    Product 1</strong></p>
<p><strong>    Product 2</strong></p>
<p><strong>    Product 3</strong></p>
<p><strong>    Product <em>n</em></strong></p>
<p>Even with this simple architecture,<strong> Information Architecture</strong> planning is very critical as architectural decisions we make at this stage can impact us at every stage of development moving forward.</p>
<h3>Activity</h3>
<p>Using the templates we just created, we'll create items which will make up our basic <strong>Information Architecture</strong>.  Since we already have our home item and data templates configured from previous activities, we only need to create the product items.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Let's start by selecting our My First Site Exercise item in the tree.  If we set our Insert Options correctly, we should now have the Product data template available to us in the Insert Section of the ribbon.<br />
  <br />
  <img style="width: 350px; height: 293px;border: #000000 1px solid;" alt="Screenshot 1" src="~/media/DAC8489060BE48458C82BE4B31FAEBC6.ashx" /><br />
  <br />
  NOTE:  We can achieve the same result by right-clicking on a item and selecting <strong>Insert</strong>.<br />
  <br />
  </li>
  <li>A dialog will appear asking you to provide a name for your new <strong>Product </strong>item.  Input a product of your choosing and click OK.  <br />
  <br />
  <img style="width: 350px; height: 125px;border: #000000 0px solid;" alt="Screenshot 2" src="~/media/087302A701B046C4AF81B18C4C093626.ashx" /><br />
  <br />
  </li>
  <li>Repeat steps 1 and 2 to create another product of your choosing.  NOTE:  Once we've built out our presentation, you'll also be testing the "Insert New Item" process as a business user from the Page Editor.</li>
  <li>When complete, your IA should look something like this.<br />
  <br />
  <img style="width: 250px; height: 337px;border: #000000 1px solid;" alt="Screenshot 3" src="~/media/170BF313DF4043B7A173A172D62F2282.ashx" /><br />
  <br />
  </li>
</ol>
